# Engineering Foundations

Before writing or reviewing code:

- Reuse before creating; extract when the same pattern appears twice.
- Explicit types at boundaries; types document intent.
- Name by responsibility; use project suffixes (`*Page.tsx`, `use*.ts`, …).
- Place code by feature layer; shared vs feature-local obvious from path.
- Separate data, orchestration, presentation, and I/O.
- Couple what changes together; decouple what changes for different reasons.

Load `.cursor/skills/foundations/engineering/SKILL.md` for decisions; load `references/` only when a principle needs deep guidance. Downstream rules must not repeat these bullets — they reference this foundation.
